#compdef ropee
# ============================================================================
# ropee - scalable Prometheus remote-storage adapter
#          for Splunk (Go, Apache-2.0)
#
# Author : DaoCloud / kebe7jun
# Upstream: https://github.com/DaoCloud/ropee
#
# `ropee` is a Prometheus remote-write + remote-read
# adapter that forwards metrics to Splunk's HTTP Event
# Collector (HEC) for long-term storage + correlation
# with Splunk-indexed log data. It runs as a single
# binary listening on a configurable HTTP port,
# implements the standard Prometheus remote_write +
# remote_read protocol (Snappy-compressed protobuf
# payloads), and translates between Prometheus's
# `samples + labels` data model and Splunk's metrics-
# index document model.
#
# Use case: feed long-running Prometheus metric series
# into Splunk for retention + cross-correlation with
# logs without giving up Prometheus's native PromQL
# query interface for short-window monitoring.
#
# Usage:
#   ropee [flags]
#
# Flags (Go stdlib flag.* parsing):
#   --listen-addr <addr:port>      - HTTP listen
#                                     address
#                                     (default
#                                     127.0.0.1:9970)
#   --splunk-url <url>             - Splunk management
#                                     URL (default
#                                     https://127.0.0.1:8089)
#   --splunk-hec-url <url>         - Splunk HTTP Event
#                                     Collector URL
#                                     (default
#                                     https://127.0.0.1:8088)
#   --splunk-hec-token <token>     - HEC bearer token
#                                     (required for
#                                     ingestion)
#   --splunk-metrics-index <name>  - Splunk metrics
#                                     index name
#                                     (default "*")
#   --splunk-metrics-sourcetype <type>
#                                  - sourcetype label
#                                     (default
#                                     DaoCloud_promu_metrics)
#   --timeout <seconds>            - per-request
#                                     timeout in
#                                     seconds (default
#                                     60)
#   --log-file-path <path>         - log file
#                                     directory
#                                     (default
#                                     /var/log; use
#                                     "-" for stdout)
#   --debug                        - enable debug-
#                                     level logging
#
# The golang/snappy lane is built on `github.com/
# golang/snappy v0.0.1` (declared at upstream go.mod
# HEAD as a direct dep, used in main.go to decompress
# inbound Prometheus remote_read + remote_write
# request bodies), the canonical Go Snappy library by
# the Go core team - github.com/golang/snappy, 1500+
# stars.
#
# golang/snappy has a specific provenance story
# inside the Go ecosystem:
#   1. The Go core team originally developed Snappy
#      bindings as part of `golang/leveldb` (the Go
#      port of Google's LevelDB key-value store)
#      around 2012
#   2. The Snappy code was extracted from leveldb
#      into a standalone `golang/snappy` repo in 2016
#      to make it usable outside the LevelDB use case
#   3. Maintenance has stayed with the Go core team
#      since extraction, but the repo is intentionally
#      low-velocity: Snappy v1 is fully stable so the
#      library only needs incident-driven security
#      patches
#
# This makes golang/snappy a *core-team-maintained-
# subrepo-style* canonical, similar to the
# `golang.org/x/*` packages but without the `x/`
# prefix because Snappy predates the formal
# `golang.org/x/*` namespace. The library is depended
# on by:
#   - Prometheus (remote_read + remote_write)
#   - Thanos (object-storage block compression)
#   - VictoriaMetrics (storage compression)
#   - InfluxDB v1 (Snappy + zstd dual paths)
#   - Cortex / Mimir (multi-tenant Prometheus)
#   - Loki (chunk compression)
#   - Bleve (full-text index segment compression)
#   - golang/leveldb (the original use case)
#   - ropee (THIS BINARY)
#
# ropee uses `snappy.Decode(nil, compressed)` to
# decompress the inbound Prometheus protobuf payload
# before passing it to `proto.Unmarshal` for
# protobuf parsing. The remote_read response path
# also re-encodes via `snappy.Encode` to match the
# Prometheus client's expected wire format.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 253 :: Snappy compression (Google fast LZ77
#              variant, optimized for decompression
#              throughput)
# Round 1458 :: Go slot 2 of 4 :: continues Axis 253
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis:
#   Rust    : BurntSushi/rust-snappy      [R1457 _avml]
#   Go      : golang/snappy               [R1458 THIS FILE]
#   TS/Node : @node-rs/snappy             [R1459 closing]
#             (napi-rs binding to
#              BurntSushi/rust-snappy)
#
# golang/snappy is structurally interesting because
# of its *extracted-from-leveldb-port* origin. The
# three lanes form a clean spectrum of Snappy
# implementation paths:
#
#   - Rust (BurntSushi/rust-snappy): line-by-line
#     safe-Rust port of Google's reference C++
#     library; preserves byte-identical output
#     vs the reference; part of Gallant's broader
#     canonical-Rust footprint
#   - Go (golang/snappy): Go core team port,
#     originally inside `golang/leveldb` (the Go
#     LevelDB port), extracted in 2016; maintenance
#     intentionally low-velocity because Snappy v1
#     is stable
#   - Node (@node-rs/snappy): napi-rs binding to
#     BurntSushi/rust-snappy; inherits Gallant's
#     Rust impl through N-API
#
# The Rust + Node lanes converge on the same
# BurntSushi/rust-snappy implementation - the Node
# slot delegates to the Rust slot via napi-rs binding.
# This Node-binds-to-Rust pattern is structurally
# identical to:
#   - Axis 244 (Argon2): @node-rs/argon2 binds to
#     RustCrypto argon2
#   - Axis 249 (QUIC): @chainsafe/libp2p-quic binds
#     to ChainSafe's quinn-rs fork
#
# The Go slot deliberately stays separate from the
# Rust + Node convergence because of Go's stronger
# preference for pure-Go cross-compile (no FFI / no
# napi). The trade-off: the Go core team has to
# maintain its own port independently, but Go
# binaries stay statically-linkable + cross-compile-
# friendly without per-target build complexity.
#
# Cross-language interop at the wire format level -
# Snappy bitstream produced by BurntSushi/rust-snappy
# + golang/snappy + @node-rs/snappy decompresses
# byte-identically through any of the others. Google's
# canonical test corpus validates this cross-library
# byte-equivalence.
# ============================================================================

_ropee() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    _arguments -s -S \
        '--listen-addr[HTTP listen address (default 127.0.0.1:9970)]:addr:' \
        '--splunk-url[Splunk management URL]:url:' \
        '--splunk-hec-url[Splunk HEC URL]:url:' \
        '--splunk-hec-token[HEC bearer token]:token:' \
        '--splunk-metrics-index[Splunk metrics index name]:name:' \
        '--splunk-metrics-sourcetype[sourcetype label]:type:' \
        '--timeout[per-request timeout in seconds]:seconds:' \
        '--log-file-path[log file directory (- = stdout)]:path:_files -/' \
        '--debug[enable debug-level logging]' \
        '(- *)-h[print help]'
}

_ropee "$@"
